<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Skeleton</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Hymedesmioid skeleton made by large choanosomal subtylostyles making the sponge surface hispid and by perpendicular acanthostyles with their bases attached on substrate. Ectosomal subtylostyles arranged perpendicular to surface with tips outward. Anchorate unguiferous isochelae and sigmoid microscleres roughly dispersed throughout the sponge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Spicules</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Choanosomal subtylotyles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Spicules of Discorhabdella hispida sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Po- 2489). A Choanosomal subtylostyle B magnified view of base of subtylostyle C-E ectosomal subtylostyle D tyle E tip F magnified view of tip. Note the surface is microspined. Scale bars: 300 µm (A); 50 µm (B); 10 µm (D, E); 5 µm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1076.37278.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620896" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">3A, B</figureCitation>
), long slightly curved near the base, maximum diameter at the base gradually tapering to sharp point (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Spicules of Discorhabdella hispida sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Po- 2489). A Choanosomal subtylostyle B magnified view of base of subtylostyle C-E ectosomal subtylostyle D tyle E tip F magnified view of tip. Note the surface is microspined. Scale bars: 300 µm (A); 50 µm (B); 10 µm (D, E); 5 µm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1076.37278.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620896" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">3A</figureCitation>
). Base smooth and slightly lumpy (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Spicules of Discorhabdella hispida sp. nov., holotype (NSMT-Po- 2489). A Choanosomal subtylostyle B magnified view of base of subtylostyle C-E ectosomal subtylostyle D tyle E tip F magnified view of tip. Note the surface is microspined. Scale bars: 300 µm (A); 50 µm (B); 10 µm (D, E); 5 µm (F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1076.37278.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620896" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">3B</figureCitation>
). Size, 814-1500 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in length, 42.0-56.5 (50.3) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in shaft width, 52.4-70.8 (61.7) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in base width.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1076.37278.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620896" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="67">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Spicules of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ise &amp; Vacelet &amp; Izumi &amp; Woo &amp; Tan" authorityYear="2021" class="Demospongiae" family="Crambeidae" genus="Discorhabdella" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Discorhabdella hispida" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="67" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="hispida">
